'''Peter Karl Lamont''' is a [[Research Fellow]] at the [[University of Edinburgh]], working on the [[history]], [[theory]] and [[performance]] of [[Magic (illusion)|magic]].<ref>[http://www.ppls.ed.ac.uk/psychology/people/peter-lamont "Peter Lamont"]. [[University of Edinburgh]].</ref> He is an award-winning [[Magician (illusion)|magician]], Member of [[The Magic Circle (organisation)|The Magic Circle]], and a former [[president]] of the [[Edinburgh]] [[The Magic Circle (organisation)|Magic Circle]]. He has performed and lectured across the world.

He is the author of ''The Rise of the Indian Rope Trick: The Biography of a Legend'', which discusses the [[Indian rope trick]], and ''The first psychic: the peculiar mystery of a Victorian wizard '', which traces the life and times of the "first psychic" [[Daniel Dunglas Home]], a Scottish medium, born in [[Edinburgh]].

